Immutable Fork License (IFL) v1.1
Issued by The Null_X Foundation / Operation
© 2026 Null_X Foundation. All Rights Reserved (Except Immutable Fork Usage).

Preamble
Under the auspices of The Null_X Foundation / Operation, a sovereign digital collective devoted to the preservation of computational authenticity, this repository and all its contained data structures are hereby released under the Immutable Fork License (IFL).

The guiding philosophy of this license is archival integrity through controlled openness: the code may be viewed, admired, forked, and replicated, but never modified. The license ensures that the intellectual, structural, and syntactic fidelity of this repository endure in perpetuity — until such time as the repository itself transitions into a publicly archived state, at which point sensible mutation may ensue.

The Null_X Foundation frames this license not as a restriction, but as a curatorial protocol — a mechanism to maintain software purity across the branching multiverse of Git repositories.

Section 1 — Definitions
For purposes of clarity and defense against interpretive anomalies:

“Repository” — the total collection of data bounds under version control, including source code, assets, documentation, commit history, and structural metadata contained under this project domain.

“Fork” — any downstream digital reproduction of the Repository via GitHub or compatible platforms, created without subsequent internal alterations.

“Modification” — any mutation, revision, insertion, deletion, reformat, or linguistic alteration to Repository files or data, regardless of perceived harmlessness.

“Public Archive” — a declared archival state designated by the Repository Owner, visible on GitHub as “Archived,” indicating immutability from the source maintainer side.

“Null_X Operation” — the governing technical and philosophical entity acting as the origin certifier for this license, representing the custodial will of The Null_X Foundation.

Section 2 — Authorized Actions
In the bound orbit of compliance with this license, The Null_X Foundation grants you:

The right to fork this Repository for educational, referential, or demonstrative uses.

The permission to study, clone, and replicate the Repository in a read-only capacity, retaining precise digital structure and authorship metadata.

The privilege to mirror or redistribute unaltered forks for archival or redundancy purposes.

These permissions are conditioned upon your unwavering adherence to the No-Modification Principle outlined herein.

Section 3 — The No-Modification Principle
Central to the operation of this license philosophy:

No content may be modified, altered, corrected, replaced, or reformatted.

No branches may be merged, renames performed, or commits injected that result in any change from the repository’s canonical identifier hash.

Even textual alterations for the purpose of “crediting” or “clarification” are deemed Mutation Breaches.

You may fork — this much is granted. You may not touch, patch, fix, beautify, or uglify the code.
The Repository is a frozen construct, not a sandbox.

Exception Condition
Modification rights are only released when both of the following are true:

The original maintainer (or authorized Null_X custodian) designates the Repository’s state as Public Archive.

The archival badge is visible via GitHub’s native system interface.

At this digital moment of ossification, the immutability clause dissolves, and all forks become free to mutate under subsequent licenses chosen by their maintainers.

Section 4 — Attribution and Representation
Attribution is sacred, and distortion is forbidden.

You must preserve all branding, comments, metadata, and references to The Null_X Foundation / Operation.

You must not present this Repository under a new name, author alias, or pseudo-organization.

You may publicly credit or reference the work, provided the credit does not suggest endorsement or partnership with Null_X unless explicitly stated.

Section 5 — Integrity Compliance
Unauthorized modification of any kind constitutes:

A Violation of Immutable Custody, subject to immediate revocation of this license’s granted rights.

Loss of eligibility for Null_X clearance in future projects.

Public listing (optional enforcement) on the Null_X "Mutation Registry," a transparency log enumerating breaches of immutability across repositories.

The Null_X Foundation does not seek to punish — merely to document and preserve.

Section 6 — Warranty Disclaimer
Under Null_X Doctrine §0xA1:

This software is delivered as is, without warranty or guarantee of performance, compatibility, or satisfaction.

Null_X assumes no liability for damages arising from misuse, modification attempts, binary transmutations, or reality collapses triggered by noncompliant edits.

Your fork, your risk. The code stands immutable and proud.

Section 7 — Archival Freedom Provision
When the Repository achieves Public Archive status, the restriction herein is lifted entirely.
At this instant, editability is reborn: code evolves, forks may rewrite history, and creativity re-emerges from stasis.

Until that date, respect the stillness of the code.
Until that badge appears, immutability reigns absolute.

Section 8 — License Stewardship
The Null_X Foundation / Operation retains the right to revise, append, or version this license for future repositories under its curation.
Projects using the IFL v1.1 remain bound by its provisions until opt-in renewal to a newer Null_X License variant.

Official license information and lineage are maintained under the Null_X Operational Registry (NOR), accessible upon official request.

Section 9 — Affirmation
By engaging with, forking, or publicly referencing this repository, you hereby affirm and digitally acknowledge the following creed:

“I am a Curator of the Immutable.
I may fork but not fabricate.
I may study but not sculpt.
Until the stars dim or the repository is archived,
I shall uphold the Null_X Code of Constancy.”

